BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:07fcb1ea4a95f2efe45eac818262098cb7b1dfb2@macro-calendar.local
DTSTAMP:20260603T031106Z
DTSTART:20260624T013000Z
DTEND:20260624T020000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Consumer Price Index\, Australia
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nReference period\n\nExplainer:\
 n• What it is: Consumer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in the pri
 ces paid by consumers for a basket of goods and services.\n\n• Usual m
 arket effect: Higher-than-forecast inflation is usually bullish for the 
 local currency and bearish for bonds\, because markets may price in high
 er interest rates.\n\n• Why traders care: CPI is one of the most watch
 ed inflation indicators because it can quickly shift central-bank rate e
 xpectations.\n\n• Frequency: US CPI is monthly. Australian CPI has bot
 h monthly indicator releases and quarterly CPI releases.\n\n• Notes: C
 ore CPI removes volatile items such as food and energy to give a cleaner
  read on underlying inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: CPI = Consumer 
 Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/release-calendar
 /future-releases/202606/all
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT24H
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Tomorrow: 🔥 AU ABS: Consumer Price Index\, Australia
END:VALARM
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT30M
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:30 minutes: 🔥 AU ABS: Consumer Price Index\, Australia
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:5549fa2e7c34368d1adce4f2ab1a94044c49beae@macro-calendar.local
DTSTAMP:20260603T031106Z
DTSTART:20260624T013000Z
DTEND:20260624T020000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Barriers and Incentives to Labour Force Participatio
 n\, Australia
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nReference period\n\nExplainer:\
 n• What it is: Employment / Payrolls / Labour Force\n\n• Measures: C
 hange in employment\, unemployment\, participation and labour-market str
 ength.\n\n• Usual market effect: Stronger-than-forecast jobs data is u
 sually bullish for the local currency and bearish for bonds if it increa
 ses rate-hike expectations.\n\n• Why traders care: Jobs data is a majo
 r driver of interest-rate expectations\, consumer spending expectations 
 and recession-risk pricing.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly.\n\n• Notes: For
  the US\, Non-Farm Payrolls is one of the most market-moving releases. F
 or Australia\, Labour Force data is important for RBA expectations.\n\n
 • Acronyms: NFP = Non-Farm Payrolls\; ABS = Australian Bureau of Stati
 stics\; BLS = Bureau of Labor Statistics.\n\nOfficial source: https://ww
 w.abs.gov.au/release-calendar/future-releases
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT24H
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Tomorrow: 🔥 AU ABS: Barriers and Incentives to Labour Forc
 e Participation\, Australia
END:VALARM
