BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:56b0e5fa5dfeae47312cd2532c8db411d5ca08fc@macro-calendar.local
DTSTAMP:20260603T031106Z
DTSTART:20260625T013000Z
DTEND:20260625T020000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Australian National Accounts: Finance and Wealth
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nReference period\n\nExplainer:\
 n• What it is: Gross Domestic Product\n\n• Measures: Broad change in
  the value of goods and services produced by the economy.\n\n• Usual m
 arket effect: Stronger-than-forecast GDP can be bullish for the local cu
 rrency and equities\, although the reaction depends on inflation and rat
 e expectations.\n\n• Why traders care: GDP is the broadest measure of 
 economic growth and helps traders judge whether the economy is accelerat
 ing or slowing.\n\n• Frequency: Quarterly\, with revisions.\n\n• Not
 es: GDP can be backward-looking\, so markets often react more strongly w
 hen the result changes the outlook for central-bank policy or recession 
 risk.\n\n• Acronyms: GDP = Gross Domestic Product.\n\nOfficial source:
  https://www.abs.gov.au/release-calendar/future-releases
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
